Despite weight changes being bounded, several di erent model shifts may satisfy the plausibility constraint. To guarantee robustness to model changes, one needs a way to represent and reason about the potentially in nite family of networks originated by applying each ğ‘† âˆˆ Î” to M compactly. We introduce an abstraction framework that can be used to this end. We begin by recalling the notion of interval neural networks, as introduced in [Prabhakar and Afzal, 2019].
De nition 9. An interval neural network (INN) is a tuple I = (ğ‘˜, ğ‘ , ğ¸, ğµI, Î©I) where:
