Given a concrete input ğ‘¥ = [1, 2], we observe that I(M,Î”)(ğ‘¥) = 1 and thus establish that Î” is sound. We now check if the old CFX ğ‘¥â€² = [2.1, 2] is still valid under the model shifts captured by Î”. The INN outputs ğ‘¦0 = [âˆ’0.031, 0.592] and ğ‘¦1 = [âˆ’0.051, 0.392], indicating that I(M,Î”)(ğ‘¥â€²) â‰ƒ 0. We thus conclude that ğ‘¥â€² is not Î”-robust.

